Dear Professor Phillips,
 
Please let me alert you to the Central European Journal of Mathematics 
(CEJM): www.cesj.com/mathematics. Excellent mathematical research continues 
to be carried out in Russia, Poland, the Czech Republic, Hungary and other 
countries of the region. Our journal is fast becoming the leading 
publication on the best mathematical research done in Central and Eastern 
Europe. More information about the journal can be found below.
 
We are inviting you to READ the Central European Journal of Mathematics. 
Please visit the journal web page: www.cesj.com/mathematics.
 
Please consider an INDIVIDUAL SUBSCRIPTION to the journal. Our special 
price is now only $149 per year. See more details at 
www.cesj.com/access.XXXX.
 
Also, please RECOMMEND TO YOUR LIBRARIAN that your library considers an 
institutional subscription to the Central European Journal of Mathematics. 
More details at www.cesj.com/subscription.XXXX.
 
You are also welcome as an AUTHOR. We are Central European in the sense 
that we are located in Central Europe and we offer some special services to 
authors from the region. We welcome and already publish many authors from 
across the globe. The authors, above all else, appreciate our fast, fair 
and comprehensive peer review. More details at www.cesj.com/authors.XXXX.
 
We hope to serve you as a reader, author and supporter of the Central 
European Journal of Mathematics.
 
Regards,
 
Gregory Margulis
Editor-in-Chief
Central European Journal of Mathematics
 
 
P.S. If you do not wish to receive any further information on CEJM, then 
please respond with Unsubscribe in the subject field.
 
---------------------------------------------------------------
 
WHAT MATTERS FOR READERS
 
·         one-stop place for high quality mathematical research done in 
Central and Eastern Europe
·         distinguished mathematicians sit on the Editorial Board, e.g. 
Stephen Smale (UC Berkeley), Efim Zelmanov (UC San Diego) and Ludwig 
Faddeev (Steklov Mathematical Institute); Stephen Smale and Efim Zelmanov 
are former Fields Medal winners
 
 
WHAT MATTERS FOR LIBRARIANS
 
·         a number of major academic libraries have already subscribed, 
e.g. libraries of UC Berkeley, MIT, Princeton, Yale and Harvard 
universities,
·         we bring new content; we are not just another channel for papers 
that will come to the library anyway through already subscribed journals,
·         librarians can seamlessly administer subscriptions and access to 
our journals, by using the services of Ingenta and of all major 
subscription agents
 
 
WHAT MATTERS FOR AUTHORS
 
·         every author receives fast, fair and comprehensive peer-review 
and publishing service
·         authors from Central and Eastern Europe, if necessary, receive 
extra assistance: we improve English language, structure and technical 
format of their submissions
·         the journal is covered by most major abstracting and indexing 
services
·         authors get free access to the journal for 3 months and a free 
PDF file
·         we promote each published paper to hundreds of researchers 
working in the same field
 
 
INFORMATION ON JOURNAL
 
·         quarterly
·         50-70 articles per year
·         online only
·         English language
·         launched January 2003
 
 

